data.name: Beef Stroganoff
data.quickTastyDescription: A creamy and savory beef stroganoff thatâ€™s quick and comforting, perfect for a weeknight dinner!
detailedCookingInstructions: Cook egg noodles according to package instructions, then drain and set aside.
In a large skillet, heat olive oil over medium-high heat.
Add sliced onions and cook until translucent, about 3-4 minutes.
Stir in minced garlic and cook for another minute until fragrant.
Add sliced beef and cook until browned, about 5-6 minutes.
Stir in sliced mushrooms and cook until they are tender, about 4-5 minutes.
Sprinkle flour over the mixture and stir well to combine.
Gradually add beef broth while stirring to avoid lumps, and bring to a simmer.
Reduce heat and stir in sour cream, mixing until heated through.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
data.modifiersForBase: Creamy and savory with egg noodles
